> Quoth Bob (Acess Systems) : or as I have 205/70
> > 
> In reference to using 205/70, this is the least tall tire- I get the
> following measurements: STANDARD=0.82X185= 151.7mm sidewall height from
> rim.  195/75 is 195X0.75 =146.25mm and 205/70 is 143.5mm.    Now I gotta
> ask, if you stick a later tranny (77, 78) in a 75 bus, would the smaller
> tires be of any value in giving more stock gearing?  Besides causing a
> "lower gear factor", the wide footprint means more steering wheel
> resistance at low speeds, abad consequence, yes?

the difference in size (diameter) is so small that the difference in not
noticable, but the handling sure is better.

